
Overview of verb reckon

The verb reckon has 6 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (5) think, opine, suppose, imagine, reckon, guess -- (expect, believe, or suppose; "I imagine she earned a lot of money with her new novel"; "I thought to find her in a bad state"; "he didn't think to find her in the kitchen"; "I guess she is angry at me for standing her up")
2. (3) calculate, estimate, reckon, count on, figure, forecast -- (judge to be probable)
3. (1) see, consider, reckon, view, regard -- (deem to be; "She views this quite differently from me"; "I consider her to be shallow"; "I don't see the situation quite as negatively as you do")
4. (1) calculate, cipher, cypher, compute, work out, reckon, figure -- (make a mathematical calculation or computation)
5. count, bet, depend, look, calculate, reckon -- (have faith or confidence in; "you can count on me to help you any time"; "Look to your friends for support"; "You can bet on that!"; "Depend on your family in times of crisis")
6. reckon, count -- (take account of; "You have to reckon with our opponents"; "Count on the monsoon")
